{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation","step":0},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","step":1},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place garlic in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>.","step":2},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add spinach, ricotta, pine nuts and reserved Parmesan then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 1<b>.","step":3},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Lay 1 butterflied chicken breast (see tip) on a large piece of cling film then cover with another piece of cling film. Using a meat mallet or rolling pin, pound chicken into a thin cutlet. Repeat with remaining 3 chicken breasts.","step":4},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Lay 2 slices of prosciutto vertically on a piece of cling film, so long sides are slightly overlapping. Place 1 flattened chicken breast on top of prosciutto across the middle. Spoon ¼ of filling mixture horizontally along chicken breast, leaving approx. 3 cm space at each end. Lay slices of mozzarella, approx. ¼ of the total amount, along the filling.","step":5},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Starting from the edge of the chicken closest to you, carefully roll prosciutto tightly around chicken and filling to form a log. Wrap cling film around log and twist ends tightly, removing any air. Repeat with remaining 3 chicken breasts.","step":6},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place water in mixing bowl. Place chicken logs in Varoma dish then place covered Varoma into position and steam <b>25 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. To check if chicken is cooked through, remove biggest log, unwrap it slightly, and use a serrated knife to cut through the middle. If it needs further cooking, re-wrap cling film and cook for a further <b>2-5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until done.","step":7},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Once chicken is cooked through, remove from Varoma and remove cling film, taking care to drain any excess water. Slice each log into 3-4 pieces and serve immediately with polenta and vegetables of choice.","step":8}],"usefulItems":"cling film, meat mallet or rolling pin","id":"r247618","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-9N-lg5VlK8U\/XZQIJLgkvLI\/AAAAAAAAcPs\/AgjK1Fx0ZvYiqQR88QFUkOJIMoTms1UCwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_y037SMMq9gHR42aY.png","title":"Chicken Florentine Involtini - Involtini di pollo alla fiorentina","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 garlic clove"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g frozen spinach, defrosted and drained"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g ricotta cheese"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g toasted pine nuts"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 chicken breast fillets, butterflied (see tip)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"8 slices prosciutto"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"125 g mozzarella, sliced"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"600 g water"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1149 kJ \/ 274 kcal","34.1 g","1.1 g","14.3 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["‘Involtini’ is used to describe wrapped bundles of food. Eaten across Italy, involtini could refer to meat, poultry or fish, with a filling of cheese, cured meats or vegetables. Florentine refers to a dish prepared in the cooking style of Florence meaning it features spinach. This recipe turns plain chicken breasts into a main course that wouldn’t look out of place at a dinner party.","To butterfly a chicken breast, place on a chopping board and with one hand flat on top, slice into the thicker side of the breast with a long sharp knife - take care not to cut all the way through. Then open out the breast so it is flat."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","50m","8 portions"]}